ports to track performance against targets. Ability to analyze multiple data sets to identify opportunities and category insights. Participate in category councils and business reviews to support collaboration, knowledge sharing, opportunity identification, and overall relationship development. Innovate within the procurement space; look at new ways to structure programs or categories, benefit from changes in supply market, or modify tools/processes to add value. Provide support throughout the sourcing and contracting process when necessary, ensuring seamless hand off to our clients when appropriate. Required Technical and Professional Expertise A minimum of 7 years of strategic sourcing experience, with 4+ years sourcing corporate and professional services. Extensive experience sourcing corporate services such as: contingent workforce, consulting services, financial services, legal services, recruitment services, relocation, HR services, and training. Excellent influencing and change management skills Ability to Travel 75% of the time. Prefer previous experience in a client facing / consultative role. Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise Deep business analysis and strategic thinking skills About Business Unit IBM Global Procurement has the responsibility for achieving the best overall value for IBM and our clients when acquiring or contracting goods, services, and intellectual property assets. Our mission: \"Listen for need, source with speed.\" We continually work to create value by managing costs and risks, engaging in revenue generation opportunities with our sales teams, and providing superior service to our clients as we ensure on-time delivery. Join us as we transform clients' strategies by delivering simple engagements focused on speed, leveraging digitization, cognitive insights, and innovation from suppliers to maximize value. Your Life @ IBM What matters to you when you\u2019re looking for your next career challenge? Maybe you want to get involv